Introduction

Cha Woongki is a South Korean singer and actor under F&F Entertainment.

Woongki competed and finished 4th place in the survival show WORLD KLASS, thus being able to become a member of the boy group TO1. He debuted with them on April 1, 2020 with the release of their first mini album titled "Reason for Being: Benevolence".

On June 17, 2022, WAKEONE announced that Woongki had left TO1 but was preparing for a new start.

In 2023, Woongki participated in MNET' survival show Boys Planet, where he was sadly eliminated after ranking 20th place.

Being a child actor from 2007 to 2010, playing in dramas such as 'Yi San', 'The Road Home', 'Green Coach', and 'Jejoongwon', Woongki took back this field of work in 2024 when he played a main role in the drama 'Love for Love's Sake'.

He was a contestant in SBS' survival show Universe League, where he ranked 2nd place overall, securing his spot as a member of the final group AHOF.
